ry and practice. In a bold move, we call for the humanities to reach beyond the confines of universities and engage in the most urgent debates facing humanity today - in a multidisciplinary, transformative, and constructive way. This is a blueprint for how societal change can be inclusive and equitable for the good of humans and non-humans alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCulturexStudy and teaching. 0aHumanitiesxSocial aspects. 4aCultural Studies. 4aDiagnosis of Our Time. 4aEnvironmental Ethics. 4aNature. 4aSociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aDiagnosis of Our Time.  aEnvironmental Ethics.  aNature.  aSociology.1 aHorn, Christoph, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKatsman, Anna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLippold, Anna Luisa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPelluchon, Corine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVenzke, Ingo, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2022z9783111025094oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839465707?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839465707zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839465707/original  a978-3-11-076700-1 DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-TGPb2022